cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LLMAIx Web"
message: >-
  If you use this software in your research, please cite the software and the
  associated publication using the metadata from this file.
type: software

authors:
  - family-names: "Wolf"
    given-names: "Fabian"
    affiliation: >-
      Else Kroener Fresenius Center for Digital Health, Faculty of Medicine
      and University Hospital Carl Gustav Carus, TUD Dresden University of
      Technology, Dresden, Germany
    email: "fabian.wolf2@tu-dresden.de"

  - name: "KatherLab"
    website: "https://github.com/KatherLab"

repository-code: "https://github.com/KatherLab/llmaixweb"
url: "https://github.com/KatherLab/llmaixweb"

abstract: >-
  A privacy-first web application for extracting structured JSON data from
  unstructured medical and laboratory documents using large language models.
  Users can upload files, preprocess them using optical character recognition
  or text extraction, define JSON schemas and prompts, run LLM-based extraction
  trials against OpenAI-compatible endpoints, and evaluate the extracted
  results against ground-truth data.

keywords:
  - "large language models"
  - "information extraction"
  - "optical character recognition"
  - "medical natural language processing"
  - "structured data extraction"
  - "clinical text"
  - "privacy-preserving artificial intelligence"

